Behind the scenes of a stunning union of light, sound, and the Riyadh skyline. A monumental project, hundreds of talented individuals, culminating in a breathtaking symphony by @christopherbauder for @noorriyadhfestival.
Unveiling the fruits of months of dedication at @noorriyadhfestival where art meets ambition, a luminous journey just started.
All the technique in the world doesn’t make up for the inability to notice the beauty around you.

“I know I’m a handful baby”, part of the new series “Relationship status:”, where we (@wheresaddie and @aialahernando) use self portraiture as a means of translating/exploring the private as public female experience. 
The artists use site specific real floral arrangements, alongside contemporary artifacts within the artists’ lived experiences; the personal objects strewn across the works serve both as a portrait of the modern women but also of the artists themselves, to create a feeling of longing in the work- to see what is concealed, to understand who is attached. This form of active looking implicates the viewer into the process and highlights further into the series, the role of desire as a (un)productive force.
